---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { persona, about, writing } from '../data/cv';
---

<Layout
	title={`About | ${persona.displayName}`}
	description={about.intro}
	ogImage="/images/voidbear3-w512.png"
>
	<article class="about">
		<p class="eyebrow">/about</p>
		<h1>About</h1>
		<p class="tagline">{persona.tagline}</p>
		<p>
			Void Bear is a psuedo anonymous brand that I use to write about technology,
			startups, and life. The industries I've worked and held positions in over
			the last few years, have very strict social media policies and too much
			attention brought security risks at a time that it was best to avoid it. 
		</p>
		<p>
			I've been in multiple start ups. The first failed.  The second pivoted. The
			last one was acquired.  I started off as web designer, one of those those nerds
			that knew how to center a div and make it work in all the fragmented browser engines.
		</p>
		<p>
			Many nights were lost to hacking away at learning to code. I started off wanting to
			be a hacker or game developer and instead just ended building things.
		</p>
		<p> 
			Fast forward a few start ups and jobs later; I've been a Software Engineer, Architect, Manager,
			DevOps Engineer, IT, in security, and even held a C-Level position.
		</p>
		<p>
			I'm at a point where I don't want to waste time on things that don't matter or interest me
			or align with my values. I'm looking for a place where I can be myself, that values
			hard work and rest, creative innovation, ownership and agency, work with talented colleagues,
			and a sense of purpose that brings value and delight to the world all while 
			generating revenue.  
		</p>
		<p>
			I prefer documents and working sessions over meetings and presentations. I prefer 
			taking time up front to do the hard things now to avoid losing momemtum, velocity,
			and quality later as that tends to stack over time. I prefer pragmatism over perfection.
			I prefer not to take shortcuts to avoid the unnessary debt, duress, and oncall fatigue later.
		</p>
		<p>
			To avoid burning out, I've been tickering on the side on various libraries and projects.
			I've found that I generally enjoy working on developer tooling, developer libraries,
			cryptography, automation, and research and development. I keep a homelab 
			of servers and devices to experiment with and learn from.
		</p>
		<p>
			I would love to have time or an opportunity to work on led lights, IOT, robotics, 
			AI, and other fun projects.
		</p>
		<p>
			I'm currently migrating my opensource work from the <a href="https://github.com/frostyeti"> GitHub organization</a>
			to the <a href="https://github.com/voidbear-io">voidbear.io GitHub organization</a> if you want
			take a look at my work.
		</p>

		<section class="links" aria-labelledby="about-links">
			<h2 id="about-links">Links</h2>
			<ul>
				{
					writing.map((w) => (
						<li>
							<a href={w.href}>{w.label}</a>
						</li>
					))
				}
			</ul>
		</section>

		<p class="back">
			<a href="/">← CV</a>
			<span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
			<a href="/blog">Blog</a>
			<span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
			<a href="/now">Now</a>
		</p>
	</article>
</Layout>

<style>
	.about {
		max-width: 62ch;
		padding-top: 6px;
	}

	.eyebrow {
		margin: 0 0 8px;
		color: var(--muted);
		font-family: var(--mono);
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}

	h1 {
		margin: 0 0 8px;
		font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	}

	.tagline {
		margin: 0 0 18px;
		color: var(--accent-strong);
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.45;
	}

	.intro {
		margin: 0 0 18px;
		color: var(--muted);
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	.para {
		margin: 0 0 14px;
		color: var(--text);
		line-height: 1.75;
	}

	.links {
		margin-top: 28px;
		padding-top: 22px;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
	}

	.links h2 {
		margin: 0 0 12px;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.links ul {
		margin: 0;
		padding-left: 1.2rem;
		color: var(--muted);
	}

	.links li {
		margin: 8px 0;
	}

	.links a {
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.back {
		margin: 32px 0 0;
		color: var(--muted);
	}

	.sep {
		opacity: 0.55;
		padding: 0 0.5rem;
	}
</style>
